WEBVTT

00:09.676 --> 00:11.476
Perfect.

00:11.478 --> 00:14.078
Hello, my name
is joe pera.

00:14.080 --> 00:15.347
-We got to go.
-What?

00:15.349 --> 00:16.749
We got to get out of town.

00:16.751 --> 00:19.217
Grab your bug-out bag and be
in my truck in 90 seconds.

00:19.219 --> 00:20.485
What's going on?

00:20.487 --> 00:23.021
I'm not sure.
We just need to leave.

00:23.023 --> 00:25.223
Okay.

00:25.225 --> 00:26.959
You want me to bring
those leftovers?

00:26.961 --> 00:28.627
Sarah: No!

00:28.629 --> 00:30.695
Let's go visit
the melskys.

00:30.697 --> 00:33.165
I don't know the answer,
but that's not it.

00:33.167 --> 00:34.566
Joe: Yeah.

00:34.568 --> 00:36.501
I couldn't believe it yesterday
when they brought up

00:36.503 --> 00:38.437
Arming us teachers at
the faculty meeting.

00:38.439 --> 00:40.639
Just a conversation,
I guess.

00:40.641 --> 00:43.508
There have been a lot
of school shootings this year.

00:43.510 --> 00:46.378
You teaching choir
with a gun?

00:46.380 --> 00:47.912
Society's sick.

00:47.914 --> 00:51.115
Then I got home and saw
how far down the market was.

00:51.117 --> 00:52.517
People are losing faith.

00:52.519 --> 00:54.586
Chinese manufacturing's
slowing, sure,

00:54.588 --> 00:57.790
But that big a dip
in a week?

00:57.792 --> 00:59.724
I couldn't sleep
at all last night.

00:59.726 --> 01:01.926
Sorry.
If you had called,

01:01.928 --> 01:03.862
I could have told you
some quiet facts

01:03.864 --> 01:06.264
About how the first known
chairs date back

01:06.266 --> 01:08.801
To ancient egypt,
5,000 years ago.

01:08.803 --> 01:11.269
What did people sit
on before then?

01:11.271 --> 01:15.073
Stools, floors,
the ground.

01:15.075 --> 01:19.611
Well, lucky for you, I got
some folding chairs in the back.

01:19.613 --> 01:21.746
I just feel like something's
going to happen soon,

01:21.748 --> 01:25.217
And I just want to be as far
away as possible from people.

01:25.219 --> 01:29.287
Okay.
Camping sounds fun.

01:29.289 --> 01:31.223
Maybe we'll see
that three-antler deer

01:31.225 --> 01:33.558
There's been rumors about.

01:33.560 --> 01:39.231
♪♪

01:41.568 --> 01:46.371
Sarah's fears, although
abstract, aren't unwarranted.

01:46.373 --> 01:49.908
This area has known
its share of tragedies,

01:49.910 --> 01:52.977
Many of them fire related.

01:52.979 --> 01:58.316
Our st. Peter's cathedral
burnt down in 1879,

01:58.318 --> 02:01.720
And then again in 1935.

02:01.722 --> 02:04.189
The presbyterian church
on front street

02:04.191 --> 02:06.525
Burned in 1931.

02:06.527 --> 02:08.993
And in the great fire
of marquette,

02:08.995 --> 02:12.531
More than 100 buildings
went up in flames.

02:12.533 --> 02:16.201
So I suppose I understand
her impulse

02:16.203 --> 02:17.670
To want to get away.

02:17.672 --> 02:21.606
Every now and then,
the town goes up in flames.

02:21.608 --> 02:25.344
Besides, it's really
nice out here.

02:33.820 --> 02:35.287
Bummer.

02:35.289 --> 02:38.156
Didn't spot
the three-antler deer.

02:38.158 --> 02:41.226
Joe, what is this?

02:41.228 --> 02:42.895
Aren't you?

02:42.897 --> 02:45.097
You definitely took something
important out of the bug-out bag

02:45.099 --> 02:48.100
So this could fit.

02:48.102 --> 02:49.768
I'm sorry.

02:49.770 --> 02:51.503
It's okay.

02:51.505 --> 02:55.173
I'm gonna see if I can catch us
something for dinner.

02:55.175 --> 02:58.711
When you get back, there'll be
a great fire to cook it on.

03:15.329 --> 03:17.596
All right.

03:17.598 --> 03:21.065
I'd love to make
this thing freaking huge.

03:21.067 --> 03:24.669
You'd probably like
to see that to.

03:24.671 --> 03:28.006
Where does that urge come from?

03:28.008 --> 03:31.610
If I had to say one sentence
that most people in the world

03:31.612 --> 03:38.083
Would probably agree with,
it'd be, "fire is cool."

03:38.085 --> 03:42.554
When the first baptist church
burned down in 1965,

03:42.556 --> 03:45.824
Many people in marquette
brought sandwiches and coffee

03:45.826 --> 03:50.094
And made a day out of watching
the church burn down.

03:50.096 --> 03:53.766
Why? They were probably
just trying to figure out

03:53.768 --> 03:57.035
Why so many of our town's
churches burn down.

03:57.037 --> 04:00.038
In this case,
it was an overheated pipe.

04:00.040 --> 04:03.241
But folks can get imaginative
connecting dots,

04:03.243 --> 04:05.043
Like gene's friend, timeric,

04:05.045 --> 04:09.047
Who thinks the three-antler
deer is an old testament demon.

04:09.316 --> 04:11.784
[ birds squawking ]

04:21.462 --> 04:23.462
♪♪

04:23.464 --> 04:25.263
[ sarah sighs ]

04:25.265 --> 04:32.070
♪♪

04:32.072 --> 04:38.743
♪♪

04:38.745 --> 04:40.412
[ tackle box thuds ]

04:40.414 --> 04:42.747
I got a rainbow trout
and brown trout.

04:42.749 --> 04:46.485
Amazing. It's like the lake
knew our fish order.

04:46.487 --> 04:48.821
Can I give you a hand?

04:53.227 --> 04:55.361
It's dinnertime.

05:00.501 --> 05:02.567
Any news?

05:02.569 --> 05:05.237
Nothing on the radio.

05:05.239 --> 05:09.441
You still feel like
something's going to happen?

05:09.443 --> 05:11.577
I don't know.

05:15.782 --> 05:19.852
Well, how many yams
do you want?

05:19.854 --> 05:22.721
You think I'm going to eat more
than one of those?

05:24.258 --> 05:27.259
Did you know that the discovery
of cooking food

05:27.261 --> 05:29.194
Made our brains bigger?

05:29.196 --> 05:30.462
I did.

05:30.464 --> 05:32.665
That was, what,
400,000 years ago?

05:32.667 --> 05:34.066
Yeah.

05:34.068 --> 05:38.470
So imagine how much smarter
you'd get if you ate two yams.

05:38.472 --> 05:41.607
I'm not gonna eat
two yams.

05:44.545 --> 05:45.810
Lucky me.

05:45.812 --> 05:49.147
Fish fry two nights
in a row.

05:49.149 --> 05:52.684
Did you go by yourself again
last night?

05:52.686 --> 05:55.620
It's tradition.

05:55.622 --> 05:57.622
I know I'm not your
grandmother,

05:57.624 --> 05:59.424
But I'll go with
you next Friday

05:59.426 --> 06:01.426
If I can get out of
detention duty.

06:01.428 --> 06:04.763
Only if you promise
to call me next time

06:04.765 --> 06:09.434
You get uneasy feelings
like you had last night.

06:09.436 --> 06:11.770
Sorry if you don't want to,

06:11.772 --> 06:14.973
But is there someone else
you could talk to?

06:14.975 --> 06:17.776
Yeah.

06:17.778 --> 06:21.513
Talking with gene helps me
when I'm wound up.

06:21.515 --> 06:23.782
One time, I almost
didn't chaperone

06:23.784 --> 06:25.183
A field trip
downstate

06:25.185 --> 06:30.188
Because I accidentally watched
"final destination 5."

06:30.190 --> 06:32.257
I was horrified
the mackinac bridge

06:32.259 --> 06:35.060
Would collapse
when the bus went over.

06:35.062 --> 06:40.599
But gene said, "don't worry,
the bridge will collapse."

06:40.601 --> 06:43.068
Well, how did he know?

06:43.070 --> 06:44.803
I don't know.

06:48.142 --> 06:50.142
Why did you trust him?

06:50.144 --> 06:51.944
Don't you trust people?

06:51.946 --> 06:54.079
No, not in
a general sense.

06:56.283 --> 06:57.950
I mean, you know why.

06:57.952 --> 07:01.420
After my brother was trampled,
I just wanted to be alone,

07:01.422 --> 07:04.823
I didn't walk
over a kid.

07:04.825 --> 07:08.560
My parents got distant
and I just...

07:08.562 --> 07:10.829
Learned to do
things myself.

07:18.705 --> 07:22.907
Was that when you started
hoarding soap under your bed?

07:22.909 --> 07:24.242
Yeah.

07:24.244 --> 07:27.312
You know, I liked
to do other stuff, too.

07:27.314 --> 07:31.115
I read a lot of books
and played a lot of video games.

07:31.117 --> 07:32.785
Very cool.

07:32.787 --> 07:35.920
You know
I played my french horn.

07:35.922 --> 07:37.722
What about
your stand partners?

07:37.724 --> 07:39.591
You get along with them?

07:39.593 --> 07:43.328
Mm. French horn players
are weirdos.

07:43.330 --> 07:45.130
Then I joined rotc

07:45.132 --> 07:47.532
To toughen up and learn
some survival skills,

07:47.534 --> 07:49.734
But I didn't buy in.

07:49.736 --> 07:53.938
It's so funny to
think of you as a goth in rotc.

07:53.940 --> 07:56.141
Yeah, we're actually
pretty all right with it,

07:56.143 --> 07:59.744
But I didn't make
any real connections.

07:59.746 --> 08:01.880
There was this guy
in the unit.

08:01.882 --> 08:06.018
You remember that song
"last resort" by papa roach?

08:06.020 --> 08:08.220
-Yes.
-So, when it would come on,

08:08.222 --> 08:11.556
He'd make everyone laugh
by putting a gun in his mouth

08:11.558 --> 08:14.092
And thrashing his head
to the beat.

08:14.094 --> 08:15.360
What?

08:15.362 --> 08:16.695
[ chuckles ]

08:16.697 --> 08:18.763
[ laughs ]
oh, my gosh.

08:18.765 --> 08:20.766
I hope he's doing
all right.

08:23.303 --> 08:25.904
I don't think people
are bad, just --

08:25.906 --> 08:28.173
[ cell phone buzzing ]

08:33.313 --> 08:34.980
Hi, gene.

08:37.117 --> 08:38.751
Oh, crap.

08:41.055 --> 08:45.124
Apple turnovers are two
for one at econofoods.

08:47.327 --> 08:49.794
I can't right now.

08:49.796 --> 08:51.463
How is everything else?

08:51.465 --> 08:54.066
Great. I sold two chairs
this week.

08:54.068 --> 08:56.000
Congrats.

08:56.002 --> 09:00.072
I'll call you soon,
but thanks for having my back.

09:04.811 --> 09:07.612
Well...

09:07.614 --> 09:10.615
All's well.

09:10.617 --> 09:14.219
And we got apple turnovers
waiting for us.

09:14.221 --> 09:17.556
I appreciate
you going with me on this.

09:17.558 --> 09:19.758
Yeah.

09:19.760 --> 09:23.762
You're a person of action.
I appreciate that.

09:23.764 --> 09:26.899
And also how you know
how to do stuff.

09:26.901 --> 09:29.568
Except for season food.

09:29.570 --> 09:32.237
We're cooking with butter.

09:32.239 --> 09:34.106
Not enough.

09:34.108 --> 09:35.107
Here.

09:35.109 --> 09:37.976
I got some salt and pepper
in my pocket.

09:44.118 --> 09:47.052
I could probably stand
to make some friends.

09:49.256 --> 09:56.461
♪♪

09:56.463 --> 09:59.264
[ blowing ]

09:59.266 --> 10:04.736
♪♪

10:04.738 --> 10:10.208
♪♪

