<i> Joe: During marquette's</i>
<i> great fire of 1868,</i>

10:13.414 --> 10:17.081
<i> Peter white,</i>
<i> the prominent local businessman</i>

10:17.083 --> 10:19.351
<i> After whom our library</i>
<i> is named,</i>

10:19.353 --> 10:22.220
<i> Took all the town's</i>
<i> banking records and cash</i>

10:22.222 --> 10:24.823
<i> And sent them out</i>
<i> on a boat onto the lake</i>

10:24.825 --> 10:26.625
<i> With several employees,</i>

10:26.627 --> 10:30.829
<i> Telling them not to come back</i>
<i> until the disaster had passed.</i>

10:30.831 --> 10:33.231
<i> Marquette's business records</i>
<i> survived</i>

10:33.233 --> 10:35.500
<i> And made it possible</i>
<i> to begin rebuilding</i>

10:35.502 --> 10:40.305
<i> The downtown</i>
<i> almost immediately.</i>

10:40.307 --> 10:43.575
<i> This is the only good thing</i>
<i> a banker has done.</i>

10:43.577 --> 10:50.382
♪♪

10:50.384 --> 10:57.189
♪♪

10:57.191 --> 11:00.058
<i> Just a few days later,</i>
<i> photographer</i>

11:00.060 --> 11:03.061
<i> And former state representative</i>
<i> steve lindberg</i>

11:03.063 --> 11:05.798
<i> Got the photo of the</i>
<i> three-antler deer.</i>

11:05.800 --> 11:14.206
♪♪
